"title": "5603: wages",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5603",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Payment by an employer for work done; all labourers should be paid fairly and regularly.</p>\n<h2>Laws relating to wages</h2>\n<h3>Payment should be made regularly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:14-Deut24:15\">DEU 24:14–24:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:13\">LEV 19:13</a></p>\n<h3>Regular rates of pay</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:50\">LEV 25:50</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:37\">MRK 6:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:7\">JHN 6:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:5\">MRK 14:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:5\">JHN 12:5</a></p>\n<h3>Labourers should not be defrauded</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:5\">MAL 3:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4\">JAS 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13\">JER 22:13</a></p>\n<h3>A fair wage should be paid</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:2-Matt20:4\">MAT 20:2–20:4</a></strong> <em>A normal day's pay for a labourer in NT times was one denarius.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:1\">COL 4:1</a></p>\n<h3>A fair day's work should be done</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:10-2Thess3:12\">2TH 3:10–3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:7-Eph6:8\">EPH 6:7–6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:23\">COL 3:23</a></p>\n<h3>Labourers should be content with a fair wage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:14\">LUK 3:14</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Wage earners suffer in times of trouble</h2>\n<h3>Egypt under judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:10\">ISA 19:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jerusalem under judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:6\">HAG 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:10\">ZEC 8:10</a></p>\n<h3>The world under judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a></p>\n<h2>The example of Jacob as a wage earner</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:12\">HOS 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:15\">GEN 29:15</a> <em>He agreed his wages beforehand</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:18\">GEN 29:18</a> <em>He was paid in kind</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:25-Gen29:27\">GEN 29:25–29:27</a> <em>He was cheated by Laban</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:28-Gen30:34\">GEN 30:28–30:34</a> <em>He makes an arrangement he can turn to advantage</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:6-Gen31:7\">GEN 31:6–31:7</a> <em>He accuses Laban of dishonesty</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:8-Gen31:9\">GEN 31:8–31:9</a> <em>He protests his own honesty</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:38-Gen31:42\">GEN 31:38–31:42</a> <em>He looks back on his experience.</em></p>\n<h2>The wages of God's servants</h2>\n<h3>The Levites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:30-Num18:31\">NUM 18:30–18:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:44\">NEH 12:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:10-Neh13:13\">NEH 13:10–13:13</a></p>\n<h3>Temple workers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:6\">1KI 5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:11-2Kgs12:15\">2KI 12:11–12:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:3-2Kgs22:7\">2KI 22:3–22:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:8-2Chr34:11\">2CH 34:8–34:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:9\">2KI 22:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:16-2Chr34:17\">2CH 34:16–34:17</a></p>\n<h3>Zechariah's derisory pay</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:12-Zech11:13\">ZEC 11:12–11:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:10\">MAT 27:3–27:10</a></p>\n<h3>Labourers in the parable of the workers in the vineyard</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:1-Matt20:16\">MAT 20:1–20:16</a></p>\n<h3>Ministers of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17-1Tim5:18\">1TI 5:17–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:4\">DEU 25:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:7\">LUK 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:36-John4:38\">JHN 4:36–4:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:7-1Cor9:14\">1CO 9:7–9:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:6\">GAL 6:6</a></p>\n<h3>The apostle Paul</h3>\n<p>It was Paul's choice to work freely:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:15\">1CO 9:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:7-2Cor11:9\">2CO 11:7–11:9</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:18\">PHP 4:18</a> <em>He expressed gratitude for gifts he received.</em></p>\n<h2>Spiritual lessons from wages</h2>\n<h3>Life's rewards are hard-earned</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:1-Job7:3\">JOB 7:1–7:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:7-Gal6:10\">GAL 6:7–6:10</a></p>\n<h3>The wages of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:21-Rom6:23\">ROM 6:21–6:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:31-Job15:32\">JOB 15:31–15:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:7\">ISA 65:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:6\">JER 51:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:13\">2PE 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>The freeness of God's grace</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:4-Rom4:5\">ROM 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h3>The generosity of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:9-Matt20:16\">MAT 20:9–20:16</a></p>\n<h3>The rewards of righteousness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:16\">PRO 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:18\">PRO 11:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:31\">PRO 31:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:42\">MAT 10:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:41\">MRK 9:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:14\">1CO 3:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:10\">HEB 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:8\">2JN 1:8</a></p>",
